    <h2 id="why-keratin">Why Keratin Supplementation Matters for Hair Strength</h2>

    <p>Your hair is 85-90% keratin by composition. This fibrous structural protein provides the tensile strength, elasticity, and protective barrier that determine whether your hair is strong, shiny, and resistant to breakage — or brittle, dull, and prone to splitting. Every strand of hair grows from a follicle in the dermis layer of the scalp, where keratinocyte cells produce keratin using amino acids delivered through the bloodstream. The quality of keratin production at the follicle directly determines the strength and appearance of the resulting hair fiber.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
      <span class="key-stat-num">85-90%</span>
      <p class="key-stat-txt">of hair fiber composition is keratin protein. The quality, density, and cross-linking of keratin molecules within each hair strand <strong>directly determine hair strength, elasticity, and resistance to breakage.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <p>Oral keratin supplementation works by providing bioavailable keratin amino acids (particularly cysteine, methionine, and proline) that the body uses as building blocks for stronger hair fibers at the follicle level. The key is the form of keratin used: intact keratin molecules are too large for intestinal absorption. Only solubilized (hydrolyzed) keratin — broken down into peptides and individual amino acids — can be absorbed and utilized. This distinction separates effective supplements from those that pass through the digestive system without providing benefit.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
