      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Biotin (Vitamin B7)</strong>
        <p>Essential cofactor in the keratin synthesis pathway. Deficiency causes brittle hair and nails. Supplementation at 2,500-5,000mcg daily supports optimal keratin production. Works synergistically with keratin supplementation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Key Keratin Amino Acids</strong>
        <p>Cysteine provides sulfur bonds that give keratin its strength. Methionine is an essential amino acid for keratin production. Proline maintains keratin fiber structure. These amino acids must be supplied through diet or supplementation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Supporting Nutrients</strong>
        <p>Zinc (keratinocyte proliferation), vitamin C (collagen and antioxidant support), vitamin D (hair follicle cycling), iron (oxygen delivery to follicles), and vitamin E (scalp circulation). A multi-nutrient approach yields the best results.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

