    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Keratin Gummies</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do keratin gummies actually improve hair strength?</summary>
      <p>Yes, when using solubilized (hydrolyzed) keratin. A 2018 double-blind RCT found that 500mg of Cynatine HNS daily for 90 days significantly improved hair strength, brightness, and amino acid composition. The mechanism provides bioavailable keratin building blocks (cysteine, methionine, proline) to the follicle. Intact keratin is not absorbed — look for hydrolyzed or solubilized forms.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the difference between keratin and biotin for hair?</summary>
      <p>Keratin IS the hair protein — supplementation provides structural building blocks. Biotin is a cofactor in the keratin synthesis pathway — it helps your body produce keratin more efficiently. They are complementary: biotin optimizes the manufacturing process, keratin supplies raw materials. Products combining both address hair health from two angles.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How long do keratin gummies take to show results?</summary>
      <p>Hair grows ~0.5 inches per month. Reduced breakage and improved texture appear within 6-8 weeks. Visible changes in thickness and growth rate become apparent at 3-6 months. Clinical studies show measurable improvements after 90 days. Hair supplementation is a long-term commitment.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What dosage of keratin is effective?</summary>
      <p>500mg of solubilized keratin daily (as used in Cynatine HNS clinical trials). Some products combine lower doses (250-500mg) with biotin, zinc, and vitamin C for synergistic effects. Verify that the product uses hydrolyzed or solubilized keratin — intact keratin molecules are too large for absorption.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are keratin gummies safe?</summary>
      <p>Excellent safety profile. Keratin is naturally found in the body and in common foods. No significant adverse effects in clinical trials up to 90 days. Mild GI discomfort is occasionally reported. Check the keratin source if you have protein-related allergies (usually sheep wool or feathers).</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can men take keratin gummies?</summary>
      <p>Yes. Keratin supports hair strength in both sexes. However, male pattern hair loss is driven by DHT sensitivity, which keratin does not address. Men experiencing pattern thinning should consider DHT-blocking ingredients (saw palmetto) alongside keratin. Keratin improves existing hair quality but cannot reverse hormonal hair loss alone.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is Cynatine HNS keratin?</summary>
      <p>A patented solubilized keratin from sheep wool, broken down into bioavailable peptides and amino acids. The most clinically studied oral keratin form with published data on hair, skin, and nail improvement. Products specifying Cynatine HNS use the evidence-backed bioavailable form.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Keratin or collagen for hair?</summary>
      <p>Keratin is more directly relevant (hair IS keratin). Collagen supports the scalp dermal layer where follicles are anchored and provides proline/glycine amino acids for keratin production. Ideal approach: combine both. If choosing one, keratin has more direct evidence for hair strength; collagen has broader skin/joint benefits.</p>
    </details>

